01/11/2006
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Bribes in public procurement procedures total some 143m euros a year, according to a study ordered by the Bulgarian Industrial Association. 
The group's vice chairman, Kamen Kolev, presented the findings Tuesday (October 31st), the first day of the Southeast European Economic Forum 2006 in Sofia.
Separately, Deputy Interior Minister Kamen Penkov told forum participants that 20 former senior officials, including cabinet ministers, deputy ministers, district governors and mayors, are being investigated for corruption. 
Six indictments have been handed down. 
(Standart - 01/11/06; Darik - 31/10/06)
